  "instructions": [
    "Heat the tandoor-style cooking vessel to 425\b8F (220\f).",
    "In a blender or food processor, combine gochujang, soy sauce, rice vinegar, brown sugar, garlic, ginger, and chili flakes. Blend until smooth.",
    "Add the blended mixture to the cashews and stir until the cashews are evenly coated.",
    "Heat the vegetable oil in the tandoor-style cooking vessel over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the cashew mixture to the hot oil and cook, stirring frequently, until the cashews are crispy and golden brown.",
    "Remove the satay from the heat and season with salt and black pepper.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional chili flakes if desired."
